<div class="project-text">
    <h3>The Project</h3>
    <p>Marco started from scratch. No prior experience, just a genuine interest in the product and the determination to build something real around it. I was there from day zero, working on the visual, digital and communicative side of the brand from the very beginning.</p>
    <p>Mini site, social, events, fairs, small experiments. The amaro has been growing at a steady and sustainable pace since then, every step considered but never without a bit of curiosity. From here came several other collaborations in the food and beverages world, but this is the one that taught me how to read the life of a product from its very first idea. It gave me a framework I have applied to every other product I have worked on since.</p>
    <p>It was also a real exercise in communication where best practices met real-world improvisation, and the work was always finding the right compromise between the two.</p>
